summary: In this blog post, I share my experiment at ODSC East 2026, where I analyzed talk abstracts to uncover the conference's true zeitgeist. By categorizing sessions into five key zones—agentic AI systems, LLM engineering, data infrastructure, applied AI, and governance—I reveal how AI builder culture is evolving into systems culture. I also reflect on my own workshop experience and the shifting focus from models to repeatable systems. Curious about what trends are shaping the future of AI conferences?
